The paper deals with the statistical implications of surrogate loss functions used in the context of ordinal regression. This involves studying the consistency of these methods, which is a key property for surrogate loss functions. The paper also derives excess risk bounds and compares different approaches on various datasets. Given these topics, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves statistical analysis, which suggests the sub-categories cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as possible options.
